<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>9 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RT-8609 SERIES - INSTALL - LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="IDcomponent" graphiccount="4">
        <title>LEFT REVERSE IDLER GEAR ASSEMBLY</title>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Position the reverse idler bearing gear and washer in the case, washer to the front of the
                reverse idler gear case (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029l8">Figure 218</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029l8" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029l8" filename="../figg13/G13029l8.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 218. Position Reverse Idler Bearing Gear and Washer in Case</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the idler shaft through the idler gear and washer and into the case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029l9">Figure 219</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029l9" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029l9" filename="../figg13/G13029l9.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 219. Install Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
            <specpara>
                <note>
                    <para>Reverse idler gear must be in mesh before the idler shaft can be inserted.</para>
                </note>
            </specpara>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Making sure the reverse idler shaft is seated in the bore of the support boss and forward as
                far as possible, install the washer and stop nut on the front of the shaft. Tighten the nut to 50 to 60
                ft-lbs. (68 to 81 N&#8226;m) (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029m0">Figure 220</hotlnk>). Install the plug in the reverse idler shaft (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029m0">inset</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029m0" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029m0" filename="../figg13/G13029m0.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 220. Install Washer and Stop Nut and Install Plug in Reverse Idler Shaft</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Install the auxiliary countershaft front bearing into the reverse idler gear case bore (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f13029m1">Figure 221</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f13029m1" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g13029m1" filename="../figg13/G13029m1.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 221. Install Auxiliary Countershaft Front Bearing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
